trans-unit.source: This event will be logged when DIP server will be started.
This event will be logged when DIP server will be stopped.
This event will be logged when an entry is added to the connected directory. The Initiator of this event will be the name of the profile that is doing synchronization.
This event will be logged when an entry is modified in the connected directory. The Initiator of this event will be the name of the profile that is doing synchronization.
This event will be logged when an entry is deleted from the connected directory. The Initiator of this event will be the name of the profile that is doing synchronization.
This event will be logged when a user is added while provisioning. The Initiator of this event will be the name of the application that is provisioning the user.
This event will be logged when a user is modified while provisioning. The Initiator of this event will be the name of the application that is provisioning the user.
This event will be logged when a user is deleted while provisioning. The Initiator of this event will be the name of the application that is provisioning the user.
This event will be logged when a group is added while provisioning. The Initiator of this event will be the name of the application that is provisioning the group.
This event will be logged when a group is modify while provisioning. The Initiator of this event will be the name of the application that is provisioning the group.
This event will be logged when a group is deleted while provisioning. The Initiator of this event will be the name of the application that is provisioning the group.
This event will be logged when an identity is added while provisioning. The Initiator of this event will be the name of the application that is provisioning the identity.
This event will be logged when an identity is modify while provisioning. The Initiator of this event will be the name of the application that is provisioning the identity.
This event will be logged when an identity is deleted while provisioning. The Initiator of this event will be the name of the application that is provisioning the identity.
This event will be logged when a subscription is added while provisioning. The Initiator of this event will be the name of the application that is provisioning the subscription.
This event will be logged when a subscription is modify while provisioning. The Initiator of this event will be the name of the application that is provisioning the subscription.
This event will be logged when a subscription is deleted while provisioning. The Initiator of this event will be the name of the application that is provisioning the subscription.
This event will be logged when a provisioning profile is deleted. The Initiator of this event will be the component name.
This event will be logged when a provisioning profile is upadated. The Initiator of this event will be the component name.
This event will be logged when a provisioning profile is enabled. The Initiator of this event will be the component name.
This event will be logged when a provisioning profile is disabled. The Initiator of this event will be the component name.
This event will be logged when a synchronization profile is created. The Initiator of this event will be the component name.
This event will be logged when a synchronization profile is deleted. The Initiator of this event will be the component name.
This event will be logged when a synchronization profile is upadated. The Initiator of this event will be the component name.
This event will be logged when a synchronization profile is enabled. The Initiator of this event will be the component name.
This event will be logged when a synchronization profile is disabled. The Initiator of this event will be the component name.
This event will be logged when an updatechgnum operation is performed on synchronization profile. The Initiator of this event will be the component name.
This event will be logged when an express config operation of a synchronization profile is performed. The Initiator of this event will be the component name.
This event will be logged when a bootstrap operation is performed on synchronization profile. The Initiator of this event will be the component name.
This event will be logged when an external authentication plugins are applied on synchronization profile. The Initiator of this event will be the component name.
This event will be logged when a bulkprov operation is performed on a provisioning profile. The Initiator of this event will be the component name.
This event will be logged when a job is scheduled.
This event will be logged when a scheduled job is removed.
This attribute is used to audit the Associate Profile Name
This attribute is used to audit the Sync Profile Name
This attribute is used to audit the entry Distinguished Name
This attribute is used to audit the Prov Event
This attribute is used to audit the Scheduler Job Name
This attribute is used to audit the Scheduler Job Name
